diagram.documentation: <html> <head> <style> p {padding:0px; margin:0px;} </style> </head> <body> The AOMS Use Cases and their relationships to Actors and Objectives are detailed in the following table. This comprehensive overview illustrates the primary functionalities of the system, encompassing both core operations and supporting activities. The table not only outlines the seven high-level use cases but also depicts their included use cases and use case extensions. Included Use Cases represent essential, non-optional system behaviors and actor goals that are integral to the parent use case. These encapsulated functionalities ensure a modular and structured approach to system design and operation. Use Case Extensions, on the other hand, represent optional or conditional steps within the parent use case. These extensions provide flexibility and adaptability to the system, allowing it to handle various scenarios and requirements that may arise during operation. By mapping these use cases to the relevant actors and system objectives, this table serves as a crucial tool for understanding the AOMS's operational scope, user interactions, and alignment with project goals.</body> </html>
